document.topic_text: Man arrested in Seattle after body found in El Paso County storage unit Janet Oravetz, KUSA 12:50 James Woo has been arrested for first degree murder. EL PASO COUNTY - A man wanted for first degree murder in El Paso County was arrested at Seattle's airport late Friday night as he was getting ready to board an international flight to Hong Kong. James Woo, 38, was taken into custody with the help of Homeland Security. Around 9 a.m. Friday El Paso County Deputies who were following up on a missing persons case located a body inside a storage unit at the Public Storage Facility in the 4400 block of E. Platte Avenue. The identity of the victim will not be released until positive identification has been made by the Coroner's Office and the next of kin has been notified.
